wikipedia_page.main: Henry William Barber (5 November 1841 – 10 July 1924) was an English amateur cricketer. He played thirteen first-class matches for Kent County Cricket Club and the Gentlemen of Kent between 1861 and 1864. Barber attended The King's School, Canterbury.
